snippet: Job openings grew last week while applications for unemployment benefits stayed low, bringing the Federal Reserve’s conditions for raising the benchmark rate closer to being met.
abstract: Labor Dept reports that new applications for unemployment benefits remained same for week ending Nov 7 and job openings rose in September, bolstering case for Federal Reserve to raise interest rates.
lead_paragraph: Job openings grew last week while applications for unemployment benefits stayed low, bringing the Federal Reserve’s conditions for raising the benchmark rate closer to being met.

headline.main: Strong Unemployment News Bolsters Case for Fed to Raise Rates
headline.print_headline: Strong Jobs News Bolsters Case for Fed to Raise Rates
